data.title: The Tower at Svanemøllen station.
data.meta_description: Close to Svanemøllen Station is the Minaret, which really has nothing to do with a mosque or Islam. It is the ventilation tower for Svanemøllen's sewage pump station. The tower was designed by the then city architect in Copenhagen Hans Wright (1854-1925) and built in 1906.
